{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014YGwLh2v6JR9GvJRw9QxMu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll summarize my findings:\n\nProject Overview:\n- This is a Jakarta EE 10 application using Open Liberty\n- Multi-module Maven project with the following modules:\n  1. roster-common: Shared utilities\n  2. roster-ejb: EJB module with business logic and persistence\n  3. roster-web: Web module with JSF and REST interfaces\n  4. roster-appclient: Application client module\n  5. roster-ear: Enterprise Application Archive module\n\nKey Technologies:\n- Jakarta EE 10\n- JPA (Jakarta Persistence)\n- EJB\n- CDI\n- JAX-RS\n- JSF\n- Open Liberty\n\nArchitecture:\n- Domain Model: Players, Teams, Leagues with many-to-many relationships\n- Supports different league types (Summer/Winter)\n- Provides REST and web interfaces for managing sports rosters\n\nConfiguration Highlights:\n- Uses H2 in-memory database\n- Configured with drop-and-create schema generation\n- Basic authentication configured\n- Supports multiple sports and leagues\n- Uses session-scoped beans for web interactions\n\nDeployment:\n- Packaged as an EAR (Enterprise Application Archive)\n- Configurable through server.xml\n- Deployable on Open Liberty\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project structure or code?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4262c337-5ef5-4dbe-9861-27da47319681","uuid":"6bcd7967-0821-4ff3-8d54-dee06e1cd5a5"}
