{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xg3w87UMAju71n9FCgVZcq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakartaee.tutorial.roster.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     8→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n    10→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    13→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean;\n    14→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    15→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    16→\n    17→@Named\n    18→@SessionScoped\n    19→public class LeagueBean implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→    @EJB\n    22→    private RequestBean requestBean;\n    23→\n    24→    private List<LeagueDetails> leagues;\n    25→    private List<TeamDetails> teams;\n    26→\n    27→    private String newLeagueId;\n    28→    private String newLeagueName;\n    29→    private String newLeagueSport;\n    30→\n    31→    @PostConstruct\n    32→    public void init() {\n    33→        loadData();\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public void loadData() {\n    37→        loadLeagues();\n    38→        loadTeams();\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    private void loadLeagues() {\n    42→        try {\n    43→            leagues = requestBean.getAllLeagues();\n    44→            if (leagues == null) {\n    45→                leagues = new ArrayList<>();\n    46→            }\n    47→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    48→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    49→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error loading leagues\", e.getMessage()));\n    50→            leagues = new ArrayList<>();\n    51→        }\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    private void loadTeams() {\n    55→        try {\n    56→            teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    57→            // Get teams from all leagues\n    58→            for (LeagueDetails league : getLeagues()) {\n    59→                List<TeamDetails> leagueTeams = requestBean.getTeamsOfLeague(league.getId());\n    60→                if (leagueTeams != null) {\n    61→                    teams.addAll(leagueTeams);\n    62→                }\n    63→            }\n    64→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    65→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    66→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error loading teams\", e.getMessage()));\n    67→            teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    68→        }\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public String createLeague() {\n    72→        try {\n    73→            if (newLeagueId == null || newLeagueId.isBlank()\n    74→                    || newLeagueName == null || newLeagueName.isBlank()\n    75→                    || newLeagueSport == null || newLeagueSport.isBlank()) {\n    76→                FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    77→                        new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error\", \"All league fields are required.\"));\n    78→                return null;\n    79→            }\n    80→\n    81→            LeagueDetails leagueDetails = new LeagueDetails(newLeagueId.trim(), newLeagueName.trim(),\n    82→                    newLeagueSport.trim());\n    83→            requestBean.createLeague(leagueDetails);\n    84→\n    85→            newLeagueId = null;\n    86→            newLeagueName = null;\n    87→            newLeagueSport = null;\n    88→\n    89→            clearCache();\n    90→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    91→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_INFO, \"Success\", \"League created successfully.\"));\n    92→            return null;\n    93→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    94→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    95→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error creating league\", e.getMessage()));\n    96→            return null;\n    97→        }\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public void clearCache() {\n   101→        leagues = null;\n   102→        teams = null;\n   103→        loadData();\n   104→    }\n   105→\n   106→    public List<String> getLeagueIds() {\n   107→        List<String> ids = new ArrayList<>();\n   108→        for (LeagueDetails league : getLeagues()) {\n   109→            ids.add(league.getId());\n   110→        }\n   111→        return ids;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    // Getters\n   115→\n   116→    public List<LeagueDetails> getLeagues() {\n   117→        if (leagues == null) {\n   118→            loadLeagues();\n   119→        }\n   120→        return leagues;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public List<TeamDetails> getTeams() {\n   124→        if (teams == null) {\n   125→            loadTeams();\n   126→        }\n   127→        return teams;\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public String getNewLeagueId() {\n   131→        return newLeagueId;\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    public void setNewLeagueId(String newLeagueId) {\n   135→        this.newLeagueId = newLeagueId;\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public String getNewLeagueName() {\n   139→        return newLeagueName;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    public void setNewLeagueName(String newLeagueName) {\n   143→        this.newLeagueName = newLeagueName;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public String getNewLeagueSport() {\n   147→        return newLeagueSport;\n   148→    }\n   149→\n   150→    public void setNewLeagueSport(String newLeagueSport) {\n   151→        this.newLeagueSport = newLeagueSport;\n   152→    }\n   153→}\n   154→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4262c337-5ef5-4dbe-9861-27da47319681","uuid":"57438fe0-0bbb-4749-8bd4-3751a358fea0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NFneAjq7QQDec6fuJaCnqL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakartaee.tutorial.roster.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     8→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n    10→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    13→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean;\n    14→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    15→\n    16→@Named\n    17→@SessionScoped\n    18→public class PlayerBean implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→    @EJB\n    21→    private RequestBean requestBean;\n    22→\n    23→    private List<PlayerDetails> players;\n    24→    private String newPlayerId;\n    25→    private String newPlayerName;\n    26→    private String newPlayerPosition;\n    27→    private double newPlayerSalary;\n    28→    private String selectedTeamId;\n    29→\n    30→    @PostConstruct\n    31→    public void init() {\n    32→        loadPlayers();\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→    public void loadPlayers() {\n    36→        try {\n    37→            players = requestBean.getAllPlayers();\n    38→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    39→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    40→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error loading players\", e.getMessage()));\n    41→            players = new ArrayList<>();\n    42→        }\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public String createPlayer() {\n    46→        try {\n    47→            // Generate a simple ID if not provided\n    48→            String playerId = (newPlayerId != null && !newPlayerId.isEmpty())\n    49→                    ? newPlayerId\n    50→                    : \"P\" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n    51→\n    52→            // Create the player\n    53→            requestBean.createPlayer(playerId, newPlayerName, newPlayerPosition, newPlayerSalary);\n    54→\n    55→            // Add player to team if one is selected\n    56→            if (selectedTeamId != null && !selectedTeamId.isEmpty()) {\n    57→                requestBean.addPlayer(playerId, selectedTeamId);\n    58→            }\n    59→\n    60→            // Clear form\n    61→            newPlayerId = null;\n    62→            newPlayerName = null;\n    63→            newPlayerPosition = null;\n    64→            newPlayerSalary = 0.0;\n    65→            selectedTeamId = null;\n    66→\n    67→            // Reload players\n    68→            loadPlayers();\n    69→\n    70→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    71→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_INFO, \"Success\", \"Player created successfully\"));\n    72→\n    73→            return null;\n    74→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    75→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    76→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error creating player\", e.getMessage()));\n    77→            return null;\n    78→        }\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    public String deletePlayer(String playerId) {\n    82→        try {\n    83→            requestBean.removePlayer(playerId);\n    84→            loadPlayers();\n    85→\n    86→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    87→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_INFO, \"Success\", \"Player deleted successfully\"));\n    88→\n    89→            return null;\n    90→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    91→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    92→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error deleting player\", e.getMessage()));\n    93→            return null;\n    94→        }\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    // Getters and setters\n    98→\n    99→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayers() {\n   100→        if (players == null) {\n   101→            loadPlayers();\n   102→        }\n   103→        return players;\n   104→    }\n   105→\n   106→    public void setPlayers(List<PlayerDetails> players) {\n   107→        this.players = players;\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    public String getNewPlayerId() {\n   111→        return newPlayerId;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    public void setNewPlayerId(String newPlayerId) {\n   115→        this.newPlayerId = newPlayerId;\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    public String getNewPlayerName() {\n   119→        return newPlayerName;\n   120→    }\n   121→\n   122→    public void setNewPlayerName(String newPlayerName) {\n   123→        this.newPlayerName = newPlayerName;\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    public String getNewPlayerPosition() {\n   127→        return newPlayerPosition;\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public void setNewPlayerPosition(String newPlayerPosition) {\n   131→        this.newPlayerPosition = newPlayerPosition;\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    public double getNewPlayerSalary() {\n   135→        return newPlayerSalary;\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public void setNewPlayerSalary(double newPlayerSalary) {\n   139→        this.newPlayerSalary = newPlayerSalary;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    public String getSelectedTeamId() {\n   143→        return selectedTeamId;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public void setSelectedTeamId(String selectedTeamId) {\n   147→        this.selectedTeamId = selectedTeamId;\n   148→    }\n   149→}\n   150→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4262c337-5ef5-4dbe-9861-27da47319681","uuid":"ad4e6686-9682-4a64-a18e-1d7dba9a22e9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D65dzS4raAqKM8VcNnFw3W","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakartaee.tutorial.roster.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     8→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n    10→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean;\n    15→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    16→\n    17→@Named\n    18→@SessionScoped\n    19→public class TeamBean implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→    @EJB\n    22→    private RequestBean requestBean;\n    23→\n    24→    @Inject\n    25→    private LeagueBean leagueBean;\n    26→\n    27→    private List<TeamDetails> teams;\n    28→    private String newTeamId;\n    29→    private String newTeamName;\n    30→    private String newTeamCity;\n    31→    private String selectedLeagueId;\n    32→\n    33→    @PostConstruct\n    34→    public void init() {\n    35→        loadTeams();\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public void loadTeams() {\n    39→        try {\n    40→            teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    41→            // Get teams from all leagues\n    42→            for (String leagueId : leagueBean.getLeagueIds()) {\n    43→                List<TeamDetails> leagueTeams = requestBean.getTeamsOfLeague(leagueId);\n    44→                if (leagueTeams != null) {\n    45→                    teams.addAll(leagueTeams);\n    46→                }\n    47→            }\n    48→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    49→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    50→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error loading teams\", e.getMessage()));\n    51→            teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    public String createTeam() {\n    56→        try {\n    57→            TeamDetails teamDetails = new TeamDetails(newTeamId, newTeamName, newTeamCity);\n    58→            requestBean.createTeamInLeague(teamDetails, selectedLeagueId);\n    59→\n    60→            // Clear form\n    61→            newTeamId = null;\n    62→            newTeamName = null;\n    63→            newTeamCity = null;\n    64→            selectedLeagueId = null;\n    65→\n    66→            // Reload teams\n    67→            loadTeams();\n    68→            leagueBean.clearCache(); // Clear the cache to reload teams for dropdowns\n    69→\n    70→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    71→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_INFO, \"Success\", \"Team created successfully\"));\n    72→\n    73→            return null;\n    74→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    75→            FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null,\n    76→                    new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, \"Error creating team\", e.getMessage()));\n    77→            return null;\n    78→        }\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    // Getters and setters\n    82→\n    83→    public List<TeamDetails> getTeams() {\n    84→        if (teams == null) {\n    85→            loadTeams();\n    86→        }\n    87→        return teams;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    public void setTeams(List<TeamDetails> teams) {\n    91→        this.teams = teams;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    public String getNewTeamId() {\n    95→        return newTeamId;\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    public void setNewTeamId(String newTeamId) {\n    99→        this.newTeamId = newTeamId;\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    public String getNewTeamName() {\n   103→        return newTeamName;\n   104→    }\n   105→\n   106→    public void setNewTeamName(String newTeamName) {\n   107→        this.newTeamName = newTeamName;\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    public String getNewTeamCity() {\n   111→        return newTeamCity;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    public void setNewTeamCity(String newTeamCity) {\n   115→        this.newTeamCity = newTeamCity;\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    public String getSelectedLeagueId() {\n   119→        return selectedLeagueId;\n   120→    }\n   121→\n   122→    public void setSelectedLeagueId(String selectedLeagueId) {\n   123→        this.selectedLeagueId = selectedLeagueId;\n   124→    }\n   125→}\n   126→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4262c337-5ef5-4dbe-9861-27da47319681","uuid":"f7b522ad-2d45-4d51-9351-2ec229b7b166"}
